For the benefit of posterity, on the exact same machine, the new
version which requires passing "-Wa,-muse-unaligned-vector-move" is
between 5% and 20% slower on BLAS actions and over 30% slower on some
non-BLAS actions. My testing suite can be found at
<https://www.avrahamadler.com/r-tips/r-benchmark-code/>. Version 85824
was built with Rtools43 and version 86152 was built with Rtools44.
Both use OpenBLAS 0.326 - single threaded and both were compiled with
march=native on a Sandy Bridge Intel 8600K overclocked to 5.0Ghz (4.9
for AVX calls) and with 64GB RAM.

Thanks,

Avi

